Program: Start the Week
Title: 15/06/2009
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/b00kwr5d
Last Broadcast Date: Mon 15 Jun 2009
Andrew Marr sets the cultural agenda for the week. His guests include the philosopher AC Grayling on why he thinks the 'war on terror' has led to a war on our civil rights, and the documentary maker Adam Wishart on how the NHS body NICE makes its decisions on expensive new drugs.